SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The association formed the BOMA Austin PAC to handle all political campaign activity on behalf of the assocciation.

BOMA Austin has delegated all duties commonly performed by the executive director and staff of a non-profit organization to a management company. These duties include: executie management board committee governance and support membership services publications and marketing education course management course coordination and support website content and management event management and support accounting and general administrative services.

Principal: Individuals representing business entities in the business of owning managing developing leasing or controlling real property. Allied: Individuals representing business entities that manufacyture distribute and or supply products or services to the commercial real estate industry. Professional: Members of recognized professions associated with the commercial real estate industry as defined by the membership policy. Special: Individuals meeting the qualifications of principal members except that such individuals are either 1 associated with a business entity that will not support membership in the association or 2 a principal representative who has left his her position in the commercial real estate industry and is seeking continued employment in the industry. This membership category is approved at the sole discretion of the board of directors. Non-voting membership - Affiliate: The board of directors may invite other individuals and individual representatives of other entities interested in supporting the association and the betterment of the commercial real estate industry by contributions or other support.
The board is selected by voting members at the December annual meeting.
The membership votes and approves the three officers President Vice President Secretary Treasurer and any amendments to bylaws.
The executive director reviews the Form 990 with the preparing CPA. The final 990 is then distributed to the board of directors prior to filing.

The board of directors is rquired to sign an annual form detailing potential conflicts of interest. Members of the board are asked to disclose any conflict at the tie of any significant vote by the board.
Certain other documents available upon request.
